MIDIpad - A MIDI Controller Interface
=====================================

Doing everything MIDI you want it to. And more

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Bill of Materials
-----------------

 * _1x_ HD44780 LCD Display
 * _4x_ Pushbuttons
 * _1x_ MSP430g2553

Using the MIDIpad
-----------------

### Mapping of controllers

 1. Press MENU
 2. Select "Controller Map"
 3. Move the slider/fader you would like to modify
 4. Select type, "Rotary/Fader" or "Encoder"
 5. (For Rotary/Fader only) Calibrate the controller by going to the lowest
    value, press OK, then the highest value, then OK, then center and OK.
 6. Select the MIDI CC to assign

### Linking controllers

 1. Press MENU
 2. Select "Controller Link"
 3. Move the controller you would like to assign to, press OK.
 4. Move the first controller, change mode if needed (Map, Invert), press OK.
 5. Move the second controller, change mode if needed, press OK.

### Using linked controllers

 1. Hold the SHIFT button
 2. Move the controller
